}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== The 802MBN module appears to be using two [[Skyworks]] :(''SiGe'') SE2528L / 2528L 2.4GHz power amplifiers.
*[http://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/Actiontec+Q1000+Teardown/16876/1 Teardown on '''iFixit''' (user contributed, from ''jBot'')] :"Actiontec" and "06221A+" is silkscreened on the board. ::P/Ns used in this entry are per this teardown. ::SoC P/N is [[Broadcom]] BCM6366UKPBG.
===Power supply=== The included power supply seems to be an '''Actiontec''' STD-10016U :(UL Code E225703, '''ADAPTER TECHNOLOGY CO LTD''').
